The objectives of the fund are:
* to maintain a readily available cash reserve to combat disasters which are likely to threaten the lives of people -and livestock until such time as other resources can be mobilized locally or from abroad; and
	* to assist the implementation of Employment Generation Schemes (EGS) that would support the achievement of the National Food Security.
	* budget allocated by the Federal Government;
	* donation from local and foreign sources; and
	* any other sources.
	* when it is proved that there are emergency intervenÂ­tions with budget gaps and that the gaps need to be filled urgently;
	* emergence of fast-set disasters deserving priority of fund allocation;
	* when it is recognized that projects which are certain to prevent disasters on regular basis are readily available;
	* when it is proved that the applicant requesting for grant is committed to contribute matching resources and when it is proved that conducive situation (atmosphere) for the proper use of the fund exists;
	* the agency requesting the loan is able to submit a guarantee letter from a reliable donor committing itself to replace the fund in an unequivocal manner;
	* when it is proved that the prevailing emergency situation warrants grants or loans.
	* The Administration shall be accountable to the National Disaster Prevention and Preparedness Fund Management Board.
	* ensure that the assets and financial resources of the Fund are properly maintained;
